quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,88,"And they say: "
  19,89,"Indeed you have brought forth (said) a terrible evil thing."
  19,90,"Whereby the heavens are almost torn, and the earth is split asunder, and the mountains fall in ruins,"
  20,70,"So the magicians fell down prostrate. They said: "
  20,71,"[Fir‘aun (Pharaoh)] said: "
  20,72,"They said: "
  21,46,"And if a breath (minor calamity) of the Torment of your Lord touches them, they will surely cry: "
  21,47,"And We shall set up balances of justice on the Day of Resurrection, then none will be dealt with unjustly in anything. And if there be the weight of a mustard seed, We will bring it. And Sufficient are We to take account."
  21,48,"And indeed We granted to Mûsâ (Moses) and Hârûn (Aaron) the criterion (of right and wrong), and a shining light [i.e. the Taurât (Torah)] and a Reminder for Al-Muttaqûn (the pious - See V.2:2)."
  22,22,"Every time they seek to get away therefrom, from anguish, they will be driven back therein, and (it will be) said to them: "
  22,23,"Truly, Allâh will admit those who believe (in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism) and do righteous good deeds, to Gardens underneath which rivers flow (in Paradise), wherein they will be adorned with bracelets of gold and pearls and their garments therein will be of silk."
  22,24,"And they are guided (in this world) unto goodly speech (i.e. Lâ ilâha illallâh, Alhamdu lillâh, recitation of the Qur’ân, etc.) and they are guided to the Path of Him (i.e. Allâh’s religion of Islâmic Monotheism), Who is Worthy of all praises."